The paper deals with a matching problem involving preferences, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and game theory (cs.GT). The use of approximation algorithms and integer programming suggests a focus on algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and optimization and control (cs.LG). Finally, the experimental comparison of the approximation algorithm and IP model suggests a focus on social and information networks (cs.SI).
